What you will do
Are you technically skilled and do you have an eye for detail? Then this vacancy as an operator in the field of medical devices might be for you! As an operator, you will be responsible for the machine production of lenses and performing precision operations and quality checks. All tasks require sharp vision and precise work attitude. In your work, you will follow various procedures and guidelines. In this way, you will ensure the quality of the products. To familiarize you with lens production, an extensive onboarding process awaits you on your first day of work. During the process, you will be introduced to the various procedures, guidelines, and methods of the company. After a few months, you will have the knowledge and skills to carry out your tasks independently. After the onboarding process, you will have the opportunity to specialize further in one or more parts of the production process. Does this already appeal to you? Then please continue reading!

About the company
You will be working for a high-tech international company active in the field of medical devices. The company has big plans for the future. In the coming years, they are focusing on growth and development. Due to the growth achieved in the past year, they are looking for additional support in their production.

Job requirements
Do you wholeheartedly say 'YES' to the following points?
- You have at least 2 years of work experience as an operator in the medical device industry;
- You have completed a vocational education at level 3 or 4;
- You are capable of working with a focus on quality and accuracy;
- And you are willing to work 32-40 hours. YES? Then this is for you!

What we offer you
Of course, we also have something to offer you, namely:
- A salary between €2,486 and €2,616 based on 40 hours;
- A full-time job for an indefinite period;
- A travel allowance is applicable;
- 25 vacation days per year;
- Opportunity to further develop as an operator;
- A friendly and enjoyable team to work in.

Can you no longer contain your enthusiasm for this vacancy? Then apply directly! We would love to receive your application and motivation! If you have any questions, you can always call us at: 050 - 369 43 30 or send an email to groningen@startpeople.nl."
